<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="80" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,150,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,763,789]" pageId="5" pageNumber="80">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is formed from the Greek noun 
<taxonomicName box="[923,1015,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="80" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[923,1015,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="80">Xanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and Latin noun 
<emphasis box="[1198,1325,763,788]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="80">marginatus</emphasis>
, referring to elytra with yellowish margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
